              xml:id="jeru0196.transcription"
              corresp="#jeru0196.translation">
            <p>Μαριαμήνου <unclear>ἡ</unclear>
               <supplied reason="omitted">καὶ</supplied> Μάρα</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation"
              ana="#b1"
              xml:id="jeru0196.translation"
              corresp="#jeru0196.transcription">
            <p>Of Mariamene, who is (also called) Mara</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Ossuary has inner ledge on two sides and low feet. Height describes that of chest plus that of gabled lid, with a base slightly too wide to rest on inner ledge. Ornamentation on the chest's front side consists of two metopes in zigzag frames and a broadened triglyph containing zigzag lines, flanked by vertical rows of three discs. Each metope contains a six-petalled rosette, asymetrically aligned, within concentric line circles. Segments link petal-tips. In the center of the chest's right side is an incised six-petalled rosette within a line circle, misdrawn, and a similar(?) rosette sits in the upper left-hand corner. Μαριαμήνου is the genitive of Μαριαμήνον, a diminutive of Μαριαμήνη, which is one of the many variants of the name מרים/Μαριάμ/Μαριάμη. The stroke between the two names probably represents an eta, standing for the usual ἡ καί used between double names. Μάρα is a contraction of Martha.</p>
         </div>
